title: Grateful Dead Live at Deer Creek Music Center on 1990-07-19
lineage: Master Cassettes (Maxell MX 100) Tascam 112MKII -> Korg MR-1, 1bit 2.8MHz -> USB -> Korg Audio Gate Software 24bit 96KHz -> Wave Lab 6.0 w/UAD -> R8brain for 16bit 44.1KHz sample rate conversion -> Traders Little Helper flac8 -> Tagged w/Tag & Rename
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, They Love Each Other, Desolation Row, Row Jimmy, Picasso Moon, Althea > The Promised Land

Set 2

Victim Or The Crime > Foolish Heart > Playing In The Band > China Doll > Uncle John's Band > Drums > Space > All Along The Watchtower > Black Peter > Not Fade Away, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Hot 1st Set; Pretty Good Aud Levels are nice; Phil's slightly muddled; a bit tinny, but thats a metal cassette for you; great transfer and clean up; I actually dig the crowd noise and chatter....argueably the best first set in '90...second set sucks.
jerry is rockin really not alot of the later year stuff is jerry this on! great tapes!!!!

me likey didnt know what was in store this night, but it was insane.  listening to it now, i still am amazed.  now i know why the guy outside said "dont eat all of these".  my buddy and i did.  wow. this buzz will not die, baby.
